The paper deals with efficient similarity search in dynamic data streams, which is a problem commonly studied in the computer science sub-fields of data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The use of min-hashing and locality sensitive hashing (LSH) also suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper's focus on scalable approximation algorithms and similarity measures could also place it in the sub-field of social and information networks (cs.SI).
